Help Type: topic
Topic: command

Command Overview

Object commands:
  wikigraph <wikigraph-uri-with-sdpub-locator> search <query>
  wikigraph <wikigraph-uri-with-sdpub-locator> list
  wikigraph <object-uri> get
  wikigraph <object-uri> related
  wikigraph <entity|triple|summary|chunk-uri> evidence
  wikigraph next <cursor>
  wikigraph <object-uri> pack

URI routing:
  `search`, `list`, `get`, `related`, `evidence`, and `pack` use Wiki Graph URIs, not bare filesystem paths.
  Read `wikigraph help uri` before using object commands; skipping the URI rules commonly leads to invalid commands.
  Read `wikigraph help object` to start from a URI target, or `wikigraph help verb` to start from an operation.
  Conceptually, `list` is `search` without query text, scoped by URI and filtered by `--type`.

Archive commands:
  wikigraph <archive-uri> create
  wikigraph <archive-uri> export
  wikigraph <archive-uri> estimate
  wikigraph <archive-uri> status
  wikigraph <archive-uri> index
  wikigraph transform [options]

Generation:
  wikigraph <chapter-uri> queue add --task <reading-graph|reading-summary|knowledge-graph> --accept-cost
  wikigraph wkg-job:// list
  wikigraph wkg-job://<job-id> get|watch|pause|resume|cancel|boost|set

Maintenance:
  wikigraph <archive-uri> get|set
  wikigraph <cover-uri> get
  wikigraph <chapter-collection-uri> add|list
  wikigraph <chapter-uri> status|move|remove|reset
  wikigraph <chapter-uri>/source set
  wikigraph <chapter-uri>/summary set
  wikigraph <chapter-uri>/title set
  wikigraph <archive-uri>/chapter/tree get|set
  wikigraph config status
    Prints JSON by default and does not accept `--json`.
